==English==
===Etymology===
From the Latin [[argillaceus]], from [[argilla]] ‘clay’, from Greek [[αργιλλος]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ɑ:ʤɪl'eɪʃəs/

===Adjective===
'''argillaceous'''
# pertaining to [[clay]]
#:*'''1994''': The gleam of the land is in its rocks, the fine-grained '''argillaceous''' rocks, here, not purple or grey, but green of living stone.  (Winterson, ''Art & Lies'')

